$ Column constraint_type (DBA_CONSTRAINTS, ALL_CONSTRAINTS, USER_CONSTRAINTS)

gh|oracle-patterns|/Installed/data-dictionary/constraints/constraint_type.sql||

The constraint type is a one letter flag which is one of (as of 12cR1):
  • C: → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/constraints/check[Check] constraint on a table
  • F: Constraint that involves a REF column
  • H: Hash expression
  • O: With read only, on a view
  • P: → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/constraints/primary-key[Primary key]
  • R: Referential integrity (aka → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/constraints/foreign-key)
  • S: Supplemental logging
  • U: Unique key
  • V: With check option, on a view

sa:

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/constraints[`dba_constraints`]

  → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/constraints[Table constraints]

  Primary-foreign key related data might be stored in a → development/databases/Oracle/objects/clusters[cluster].
